The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 29 November is 9,050 (1,047.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 24 November, there were 607 new confirmed cases (70.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 17 November, there were 1,070 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 43% (463 fewer cases).
